  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim is to examine the role of intestinal microbiota in the pathogenesis of chronic
      inflammatory bowel diseases (IBD)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      IBD patients to whom colonoscopy is performed will be recruited. Mucosal specimens from large
      intestine and terminal ileum will be collected as well as stool specimens. The microbiota
      will be analyzed at the microbiology laboratory and the results will be correlated with
      endoscopical, laboratory and histopathological findings.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
